The International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA) is a set of symbols that linguists use to describe the sounds of spoken languages.

This site allows you to press buttons for the IPA symbols on your phone (or other device) and have them be typed on your computer (provided you have it configured correctly).

CLICK HERE FOR INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE USAGE OF THIS SITE/PROGRAM

If the site doesn't work, make sure you're using the right key, given to you by the client.  If you are, then make sure you haven't been timed out (this usually happens after a little more than an hour of inactivity).  If you have been timed out, simply restart your client and enter the new key.
